<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 94 / EBRD to take stake in bank
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN THORNHILL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The European Bank of Reconstruction and Development is to make a Dollars 35m
(Pounds 22m) equity investment in Tokobank, providing Russia's fourth
largest commercial bank with additional capital to service corporate
clients. The EBRD, which will gain 14 per cent of Tokobank's common voting
stock and gain a seat on its council, claims this will be the first
large-scale equity investment by an international financial institution in
the Russian banking sector.
Mr Victor Yakunin, Tokobank's president, said the EBRD's investment would
help it expand its products and markets, especially for long-term credits
needed for project financing. Tokobank was founded as a joint stock company
in 1991 and has built up a network of 16 branches. The bank has 400
corporate shareholders and provides banking services to large and
medium-sized enterprises, mainly in the energy sector. As of September 1994,
Tokobank had total assets of Dollars 1bn and common share capital of Dollars
250m.
</TEXT>
