<HEADLINE>
FT  29 SEP 94 / UK Company News: Greenacre up 10%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Greenacre Group, the nursing home operator, reported pre-tax profits for the
six months to July 31 up 10 per cent from Pounds 794,000 to Pounds 873,000.
The figure was after increased net interest payable of Pounds 165,000,
against Pounds 45,000.
Turnover for this USM-quoted company rose 36 per cent to Pounds 4.52m,
against Pounds 3.32m. At the end of the period the number of beds in
operation and under development totalled 623 (575).
Earnings per share were 0.35p (0.32p) and the interim dividend is raised to
0.16p (0.15p).
</TEXT>
