<DATELINE>
   HONG KONG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Jardine Matheson has outlined the arrangements for investors to trade in
group company shares on the Singapore stock exchange following its
withdrawal from Hong Kong.
It will bear the costs of switching into the Singapore clearing and
settlement system and has further arranged with nine local brokerages to
levy a maximum commission charge of 0.5 per cent on retail transactions in
shares of Jardine companies.
Shareholders will still find the cost of dealing more expensive than in Hong
Kong, where the normal trade levy is 0.42 per cent including stamp duty and
transaction levy.
