FT  28 SEP 94 / Letters to the Editor: Strength at Saint Louis
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr MICHEL ROQUEPLO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, In the Lex column article on Arjo Wiggins Appleton (September 22)
reference was made to 'the financial weakness of Saint Louis' and the piece
questioned whether that is holding back AWA's industrial progress.
Your question is irrelevant because it is based on a false premise. Far from
being financially weak, Saint Louis has one of the strongest balance sheets
in French industry as you yourself recognised only three weeks ago.
We have gone on record recently to the effect that we have an aggressive
acquisition strategy and a war chest of FFr7bn to fund it.
Michel Roqueplo,
